<div class="row lastelement">
  <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
    <h1 class="text-center">You should learn...</h1>
    <h1 class="text-center essence">...Sprite Kit...</h1>
    <div class="top-buffer-large">
      <%= image_tag "spritekit.png", class: "img-responsive center-block" %>
      <p class="top-buffer-large">We are convinced, that your first personal game project should run on a smartphone. The reason for this is, that PC and console games usually incorporate a wide range of skills that are rarely covered by one person. Sprite Kit, a game development framework for iOS (iPhone, iPad) makes this process especially easy.</p>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-center essence"><a href="https://teamtreehouse.com/space-cat" target="_blank"> ...on Teamtreehouse.com </a></h1>
    <div class="top-buffer-large">
      <%= link_to image_tag("teamtreehousegame.png", alt: "Teamtreehouse Screenshot", class: "img-responsive center-block"), 'https://teamtreehouse.com/space-cat', target:"_blank" %>
      <p class="top-buffer-large">The best place to get a jump-start with Sprite Kit game development is <a href="https://teamtreehouse.com/space-cat" target="_blank">Teamtreehouse.com</a>. Over the course of two consecutive tutorials, you will design and create a Space Shooter game from scratch. The first tutorial will introduce you to game design, whereas along the second tutorial you will actually program the game.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="top-buffer-large">
      <%= link_to "Check out Teamtreehouse now!", 'https://teamtreehouse.com/space-cat', class: "btn btn-lg btn-primary btn-block", target:"-blank" %>
    </div>
    <div class="top-buffer-large bottom-padding">
      <%= link_to root_path, class: "btn btn-lg btn-default btn-block" do %>
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left greytext"></span>
        Start again
      <% end %>
    </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


